==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toned
<hw>Toned</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having (such) a tone; --
chiefly used in composition; <as>as, high-<ex>toned</ex>;
sweet-<ex>toned</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Toned paper</b></col>, <cd>paper having a slight tint, in
distinction from paper which is quite white.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toneless</ent>⟦br⟧
